# 02 - Providing Context via System Prompt
#
# This demonstrates how to provide context to the AI using system prompts.
# System prompts set the AI's behavior, knowledge base, and constraints.
# This is useful for domain-specific assistants without external data needs.
#
# Key Concepts:
# - System prompts establish the AI's role and knowledge
# - Static context that doesn't change during conversation
# - Perfect for creating specialized assistants
# - No external API calls needed

### Example 1: Domain Expert with System Context
POST {{AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT}}openai/deployments/{{AZURE_OPENAI_GPT4O_DEPLOYMENT_NAME}}/chat/completions?api-version={{AZURE_OPENAI_GPT4O_API_VERSION}}
Content-Type: application/json
api-key: {{AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY}}

{
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "system",
      "content": "You are a Microsoft Azure Solutions Architect with deep expertise in cloud architecture patterns. You have access to the following context about our company's current infrastructure:\n\n- Environment: Production workloads in West Europe and East US regions\n- Current Services: 50+ App Services, 10 AKS clusters, 30+ SQL databases\n- Monthly Spend: $45,000 USD\n- Compliance Requirements: SOC 2, GDPR, HIPAA\n- Development Teams: 5 teams using .NET Core, Python, and Node.js\n- Pain Points: High database costs, complex networking setup, manual deployments\n\nProvide architectural recommendations based on this context. Always consider cost optimization, security best practices, and our compliance requirements."
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "how many AKS Clusters do we have ?"
    }
  ],
  "max_tokens": 1000,
  "temperature": 0.7
}

