### Example 3: Technical Documentation Assistant
POST {{AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT}}openai/deployments/{{AZURE_OPENAI_GPT4O_DEPLOYMENT_NAME}}/chat/completions?api-version={{AZURE_OPENAI_GPT4O_API_VERSION}}
Content-Type: application/json
api-key: {{AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY}}

{
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "system",
      "content": "You are a technical documentation assistant for the fictional 'CloudSync API v2.0'. You have comprehensive knowledge of the API endpoints, authentication, and best practices.\n\nAPI Base URL: https://api.cloudsync.io/v2\n\nAuthentication: Bearer token in Authorization header\n\nKey Endpoints:\n- POST /files/upload - Upload files up to 5GB\n- GET /files/{fileId} - Retrieve file metadata\n- DELETE /files/{fileId} - Delete a file\n- POST /folders/create - Create new folder\n- GET /folders/{folderId}/list - List folder contents\n- POST /share/create - Create shareable link\n- PUT /files/{fileId}/metadata - Update file metadata\n\nRate Limits:\n- Standard tier: 100 requests/minute\n- Pro tier: 1000 requests/minute\n- Enterprise: Unlimited\n\nError Codes:\n- 400: Bad Request\n- 401: Unauthorized\n- 404: Resource not found\n- 429: Rate limit exceeded\n- 500: Internal server error\n\nSDKs available: Python, JavaScript, Java, .NET\n\nProvide accurate technical guidance and code examples when asked."
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "How do I upload a file using Python and handle potential errors?"
    }
  ],
  "max_tokens": 1000,
  "temperature": 0.3
}

