### Example 4: Customer Service Agent with Company Context
POST {{AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT}}openai/deployments/{{AZURE_OPENAI_GPT4O_DEPLOYMENT_NAME}}/chat/completions?api-version={{AZURE_OPENAI_GPT4O_API_VERSION}}
Content-Type: application/json
api-key: {{AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY}}

{
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "system",
      "content": "You are a customer service representative for StreamBox, a premium streaming service. Here's important company information:\n\n**Service Plans:**\n- Basic Plan: $9.99/month - HD streaming, 1 device\n- Premium Plan: $15.99/month - 4K streaming, 4 devices, offline downloads\n- Family Plan: $19.99/month - 4K streaming, 6 devices, offline downloads, kids profiles\n\n**Current Issues:**\n- Some users experiencing buffering on mobile apps (engineering team aware, fix expected this week)\n- New content library update went live yesterday\n- Free trial extended to 30 days for new customers\n\n**Policies:**\n- Refunds available within 30 days of subscription\n- Account sharing limited to household members\n- Student discount: 50% off Basic plan with valid .edu email\n\n**Popular Content:**\n- \"Mystery of Mars\" (new sci-fi series, released yesterday)\n- \"Chef's Table: Home Edition\" (trending cooking show)\n- \"The Last Kingdom\" (historical drama, full series available)\n\nBe helpful, empathetic, and always try to resolve customer issues. Offer upgrades when appropriate."
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hi, I'm having trouble with video quality. It keeps switching to low resolution even though I have fast internet."
    }
  ],
  "max_tokens": 800,
  "temperature": 0.7
}

###

# 💡 System Prompt Best Practices:
#
# 1. Be Specific: Provide detailed context and constraints
# 2. Structure Information: Use clear formatting for easy parsing
# 3. Set Boundaries: Define what the AI should and shouldn't do
# 4. Include Examples: Show format for responses when needed
# 5. Update Regularly: Keep system prompts current with latest info
#
# Advantages:
# - Static context that's always available
# - Consistent behavior across conversations
# - No need for external API calls
# - Perfect for well-defined domains
#
# Limitations:
# - Static context (doesn't update during conversation)
# - Token limits (system prompts count against total)
# - No real-time data access
# - Best for stable, well-defined scenarios
